This article is a joint communique between President Barack Obama and President Dilma Rousseff. They discussed various topics including trade and investment cooperation, increasing people to people ties, fostering partnerships through travel facilitation, education, energy, science, and technology, strengthening global, multilateral, and regional cooperation, and strengthening defense and security cooperation. They expressed their commitment to deepening economic engagement with Africa, supporting progress in Africa's development, and working together to promote democracy and human rights in the Americas. They also discussed the need for a negotiated and inclusive political solution in Syria, resolving the Israel-Palestinian conflict, and countering violent extremism. They welcomed the entry into force of the Defense Cooperation Agreement and the General Security of Military Information Agreement, and emphasized the importance of fighting the global drug problem and combating transnational crimes.